Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State has lauded the effort and continued support of campaign flow political pressure groups for him and the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), urging them not to relent in the drive for good governance. The governor, who spoke at the inauguration of the State Executive Council members and coordinators of the 25 local government areas in the state, disclosed that the government has always enjoyed their unalloyed support at all times. Represented by his Senior Special Assistant on Political Matters, Hon. Benson Diaso, the Okowa said he was elated with the group’s formidable resolve always to support the party and the governorship candidate in its entire ramification. In his speech, the director general and convener of the inauguration, Engr. (Dr) Bemigho Ofoeyeno, said campaign flow for Okowa was a grassroot political pressure group with a numerical membership strength of over 500,000 people spread across the 25 local government areas of the state.